StomaTrak Privacy Policy

Last Updated: October 29, 2023

-- Thank you for choosing StomaTrak. Your privacy is crucial to us. This Privacy Policy is designed to explain how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our StomaTrak application ("App").

-- By accessing or using the App, you signify your understanding and acceptance of the collection, use, and sharing of your information as described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, do not download, register with, or use the App.

1. Data Collection

-- When you use StomaTrak, we collect the following types of information:

1.1 Personal Data: This data includes but is not limited to:

-- Ostomy output information.
-- Water intake records.

1.2 Technical Data: Such as device ID, device type, operating system, and other technical attributes.

2. Use of Your Information

-- Having accurate information about you helps us provide a smooth experience. Specifically, we may use the information collected about you via the App to:

2.1 Monitor and analyze your ostomy output and water intake to ensure your well-being.

2.2 Improve the App by monitoring and analyzing usage patterns and trends.

3. Data Storage

-- Your data is stored on secure servers and is encrypted both in transit and at rest.

4. Data Sharing

4.1 We do not sell, rent, or otherwise share your personal data with third parties for their marketing purposes.

4.2 We may share your information with our trusted third-party service providers to help us operate, provide, improve, understand, customize, support, and market our services.

5. User Rights

5.1 Access: You have the right to access your personal data that we hold.

5.2 Correction: If the personal data we hold about you is inaccurate or incomplete, you have the right to have it corrected.

5.3 Deletion: You can request the deletion or removal of personal data where there's no compelling reason for its continued processing.

6. Data Security

-- We implement various measures to protect your information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

-- However, no electronic storage or transmission method is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee its absolute security.

7. Children's Privacy

-- StomaTrak is not intended for individuals under 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal data, we will take steps to delete such information.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

-- We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

-- We will always indicate the date the latest changes were published. Continued use of the App after the changes become effective means you agree to the revised policy.

9. Contact Us

-- If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: MichaelAlanWright@gmail.com
